<br>
Heres a couple of examples.  This guy trains me and makes an ass of himself.  Then I talk to someone who I didn't know was his friend.  What did they say?  &quot;Oh hes a nice guy, except when he gets angry then he can do some bad @$&amp;*&quot;.  <br>
<br>
Wtf?  I'm sorry, but if you train people when you're angry you're not a nice guy.  It only means theres periods between your outbursts where you do no harm.<br>
<br>
This happened to a friend/guildmate of mine.  He groups in H/WL in KC and the loot rules are NBG.  Hes a monk. A Tstaff drops and the leader changes the rules, against the wishes of the entire group, who thought he should get it.  Now you have to give up whatever you're using to get the item.  Well some monks use their fists, so he can't give up anything so it goes to open lotto and she wins.<br>
<br>
Then, a few days later the subject comes up again in guildchat and someone says &quot;Oh, shes really nice but shes REALLY greedy&quot;.  Well, last time I checked being a nice person dosn't constitute being greedy.<br>
<br>
Just because you don't train people when you're not angry dosn't make you nice.  Just because you don't cheat when theres nothing at stake (sp?) dosn't make you nice.  I can say the same thing for Hitler.  &quot;Oh, hes nice.  But he REALLY hates jews&quot;.<br>
<br>
Now, I understand and applaud people for sticking up for their friends.  But you don't have to dirty your names by sticking up for them.  Sure, they may be nice to you, but you don't need what they do to others reflecting off you. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFF8DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/uchassaria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chassaria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MithMarr Defender<br><img src=http://www.winterblood.com/mmdn/star2.gif><img src=http://www.winterblood.com/mmdn/star2.gif></span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#006400>(9/7/01 4:24:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=785.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: No, they're NOT nice</span><hr size=1> That's why I rarely trust other people's judgment on character.  I know several people that used to say &quot;Oh he's nice&quot; or &quot;Oh he's a good player&quot; and then the first time I group with them or run into them they are being a total moron...and the second time...and the thrid time...etc etc <br>
